 the world. We were in a building for some time, and then there was a selection and all those who were strong enough were taken to camps all around Germany for forced labors. I would always hid under beds, or anywhere to avoid being taken to labor camps."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "518.126","u": "Oh! So it was possible to hide sometimes, wasn&#226;t it?"},    {"who": "Henry Sochami", "start": "528.195","u": "It was sometimes possible. From there, I was taken to a small camp. In that small camp, I was in a barrack hut with 1,200-1,300 people. There were 7 or 8 people per square meter. At ten in the morning, we were given a liter of water and a piece of bread. Three months later, Americans were approaching and every afternoon Jews were gathered to be taken away. Christians were not taken away, but Jews were. I would hide anywhere, and I even lived among Christians and they did not know I was a Jew."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "572.930","u": "Did you carry anything that distinguished you as Jews?"},    {"who": "Henry Sochami", "start": "578.001","u": "In Auschwitz, we carried a sign as Jews, but when we were in Buchenwald we did not have anything."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "583.784","u": "OK."},    {"who": "Henry Sochami", "start": "584.677","u": "There were no differences among us."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "585.673","u": "Aha."},    {"who": "Henry Sochami", "start": "586.699","u": "Jews that were taken away from this place, were killed down the road with submachine guns. I was able to hid for three days under ground, in a barrack, together with many Russian Christians, who did not know I was a Jew."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "609.831","u": "They didn&#226;t know you."},    {"who": "Henry Sochami", "start": "610.875","u": "They didn&#226;t know if I was a Jew. I always told them I was Greek and Christian."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "615.704","u": "Greek and Christian, I see."},    {"who": "Henry Sochami", "start": "617.757","u": "Then, a couple of days before the Germans left, the Americans arrived. It was about four in the afternoon, in April; April 11, 1945."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "634.526","u": "Right."},    {"who": "Henry Sochami", "start": "635.268","u": "When I saw the Russians coming out, because we had been hiding, I did not want to go out because I was scared."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "641.456","u": "Right."},    {"who": "Henry Sochami", "start": "642.229","u": "Then I saw they were all kissing and embracing each other outside. I looked and I saw everybody was dancing because the Americans were coming, so I went out. I weighted only 38 kg because of the famine, and though I was falling down, I started singing and dancing."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "665.969","u": "Right."},    {"who": "Henry Sochami", "start": "667.200","u": "Once the Americans arrived, we started eating and drinking well, and I was with the Americans for two months."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "674.866","u": "Where?"},    {"who": "Henry Sochami", "start": "675.681","u": "In Buchenwald."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "677.009","u": "Buchenwald. I see."},    {"who": "Henry Sochami", "start": "678.790","u": "After two months, we were sent to Paris to be taken to Greece."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "683.184","u": "Right."},    {"who": "Henry Sochami", "start": "683.999","u": "By plane."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "685.418","u": "Aha."},    {"who": "Henry Sochami", "start": "687.006","u": "[Unintelligible]"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "687.899","u": "How many people were there on the plane?"},    {"who": "Henry Sochami", "start": "689.710","u": "Only 53 Greek."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "692.185","u": "Aha."},    {"who": "Henry Sochami", "start": "693.060","u": "And 10 from Salonica."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "694.388","u": "Aha."},    {"who": "Henry Sochami", "start": "695.294","u": "We were taken to Paris, and the rest were sent to Greece. And since I had served in the French L&#195;gion &#195;trang&#195;re from 1920 to 1925, in Morocco . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "707.626","u": "Oh. Right. Aha."},    {"who": "Henry Sochami", "start": "709.063","u": "I had the chance of staying in France."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "713.367","u": "Aha."},    {"who": "Henry Sochami", "start": "714.683","u": "And so I stayed like this for a year because I was really thin."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "723.242","u": "Aha."},    {"who": "Henry Sochami", "start": "723.725","u": "And now, I have started to work."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "726.351","u": "And who do you work for now?"},    {"who": "Henry Sochami", "start": "728.977","u": "For an American journal."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "730.504","u": "OK. And what are you planning to do in the future?"},    {"who": "Henry Sochami", "start": "736.239","u": "I don&#226;t know . . . For the time being, I am working here, and as soon as I can find another job to earn my living."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "746.941","u": "Aha. But, are you planning to stay in France?"},    {"who": "Henry Sochami", "start": "750.140","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "750.774","u": "And . . ."},    {"who": "Henry Sochami", "start": "751.167","u": "May be I will go to Palestine later."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "754.746","u": "Aha."},    {"who": "Henry Sochami", "start": "755.350","u": "And . . . as soon as the situation improves."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "758.519","u": "Aha. And what do you do here for the journal? What are you doing now?"},    {"who": "Henry Sochami", "start": "763.590","u": "I work here in the [unintelligible], Where they receive heavy boxes. I carry them, I close envelopes . . . er . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "771.817","u": "So you do manual work."},    {"who": "Henry Sochami", "start": "773.719","u": "Yes. Manual work."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "774.854","u": "Do you have family here?"},    {"who": "Henry Sochami", "start": "778.252","u": "Unfortunately, there were 27 members in my family: 3 brothers, one sister with their own families. And they all ended up in [crematories?], and I am the only one left in my whole family."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "793.554","u": "Aha."},    {"who": "Henry Sochami", "start": "793.886","u": "Out of 27, I am alone in the world."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "796.240","u": "And have you written to Greece?"},    {"who": "Henry Sochami", "start": "800.827","u": "Yes. I have written to Greece, but [unintelligible] told me that my brother&#226;s oldest son is alive."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "809.127","u": "Pardon me."},    {"who": "Henry Sochami", "start": "809.688","u": "My brother&#226;s oldest son is still alive."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "814.578","u": "So, he is alive."},    {"who": "Henry Sochami", "start": "815.743","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "816.365","u": "Aha."},    {"who": "Henry Sochami", "start": "816.655","u": "And one of my sister&#226;s daughters . . . people say they saw her alive with other girls . . . but she left with some Belgians, and I have no idea whether she is dead or alive . . . I don&#39;t know where she is . . . I was told she was sent to Belgium."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "833.786","u": "Oh. Right. She went to Belgium but you are not sure."},    {"who": "Henry Sochami", "start": "835.977","u": "Yes. I don&#226;t know where [unintelligible]."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "838.965","u": "Well, monsieur . . . Sochami. This has been an interesting conversation. I found all you said very interesting. Thank you very much."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "848.683","u": "[In English] That ends the report of Henry Sochami. Taking about . . . taking about twelve minutes of Spool number 43. We will leave the